title: For Sale:  PMAG 20LR 308 7.62x51 NEW
postcontent:
I have several of these in stock.

The 7.62x51 NATO (.308 Winchester) PMAG 20LR is a lightweight, cost effective, high reliability magazine for SR25/M110 pattern rifles featuring true 20-round capacity, constant-curve body, and snap on Impact/Dust Cover. Designed specifically for military-issue MK11/M110 rifles and mil-spec ammunition (including M118LR), the PMAG 20LR is less than half the weight of standard issue steel magazines and maintains a service life round count approximately equal to the rifle barrel itself.

Features

    Optimized for use with 7.62x51 NATO (.308 Winchester) ammunition with an overall cartridge length less than 2.820", including M118LR
    Additional commercial rifle compatibility includes the KAC SR25, DPMS LR308, LWRCI REPR, LaRue OBR, Bushmaster .308 ORC, LMT .308 MWS*, Remington R-25, POF P-308, JP Enterprises LRP-07, Les Baer .308, Colt LE901-16S, the new Armalite AR-10A, and others
    Impact and crush resistant polymer construction
    Constant-curve internal geometry for smooth feeding
    Specially designed, self-lubricating follower for increased reliability
    Multi-use Impact/Dust Cover keeps dust and dirt out of the magazine during storage and protects the feedlips from potential hard impact damage during transit
    High-quality stainless steel spring for corrosion resistance
    Textured gripping surface and flared floorplate for positive magazine handling
    Robust floorplate for increased drop protection, easily removable for field maintenance and cleaning


NOTE: NOT compatible with Armalite AR-10B, Noveske N6, Springfield Armory M1A, Rock River Arms LAR8, FN SCAR 17S or any other rifles that utilize M14, FN FAL, or HK 91/G3 patterned magazines.

*NOTICE: PMAG 20LR COMPATIBILITY WITH LMT MWS RIFLE
A potential compatibility issue has come to Magpul's attention regarding the PMAG 20LR magazine when used in a limited number of 7.62 NATO caliber LMT MWS weapon systems. When the PMAG 20LR is inserted into the magazine well, some MWS rifles exhibit interference between the bolt catch and the rear of the magazine. This can cause partial engagement of the bolt catch and result in unintentional contact between the bolt carrier group and the bolt catch during normal weapon operation. Although this issue has only been reported by a very limited number of end users, Magpul has introduced a slight modification to all new production PMAG 20LR magazines to eliminate any potential for bolt catch interference, effective 5/18/2011.

Magpul is committed to continued improvement of our entire product line to ensure the widest range of weapon compatibility and best functionality possible. To most efficiently handle compatibility inquiries regarding the PMAG 20LR, please contact Magpul via email at REDACTED.

title: For Sale:  Spikes Tactical AR15 AR74 w Melonite Lothar Walther barrel 5.45x39
postcontent: This is a new AR15 that will pay for itself in ammo savings, and then continue paying you back every time you buy more. It is a brand new limited production Spikes Tactical upper in 5.45x39 (AK74) caliber matched to a brand new complete milspec PSA GenII forged alloy lower receiver. It has never been fired and the fit is perfect, nice and tight. These are unofficially referred to as a "AR74" and are a very smart buy due to the similar caliber ammo they take which is plentiful and at a much lower cost. It has a top quality Lothar Walther barrel ($375 alone) and complete corrosion resistance treatment, specifically designed to chew through cheap surplus 5.45x39 ammo that is still widely available and only costs $160-$180 per 1080 round can. You will save approximately $500 or more per 1000 rounds compared to .223 / 5.56, so buy the time you have purchased 3 of the 1080 round cans you have saved the entire cost of the rifle, basically making it free. After that, it will continue to pay you back by saving you another $500 or so on every 1080 round can purchased. Instead of feeling gouged when trying to buy some ammo just to go shoot your rifle for the day, you can enjoy taking advantage of the minimal cost of your ammo making it a pleasant experience. This gives you an affordable way to stock up on ammo for your AR15, you can stack it deep in sealed cans and have a lifetime supply for that price. Shoot 3-4 times the amount of ammo (in a better round) than your buddies can with their AR15s for the same cost. You can even afford to waste I mean shoot your ammo using one of those SlideFire stocks with this set up if that is your thing. The 5.45x39 has a very flat trajectory and nearly identical velocity to 5.56, but tumbles violently on impact due to bullet design (as opposed to cleanly passing straight through like 5.56 can). It produces much more devastating wounds, and over-penetration should never be an issue with this caliber. Some people prefer it for home defense due to that fact alone. This is by far the cheapest military spec'd ammo there is to my knowledge. Some batches of this ammo may be corrosive, which really doesn't matter if you clean your rifle after shooting, but in case you cant or don't, this limited edition Spikes Tactical Corrosion Resistant upper has the following features: Melonite finish inside and out, Lothar Walther Barrel with Nickel Boron M4 Extension, Melonite coated F-marked FSB, Melonite coated Gas Tube (stainless roll pin), and Melonite coated A2 Flash Hider. I saw a video recently of a guy that shot 7500 rounds of corrosive surplus ammo through one of these Melonite treated uppers over the course of a year without cleaning the rifle. When he finally did there was zero corrosion present due to the anti-corrosion Melonite finish. Lower is complete milspec Palmetto State Armory, with a nice trigger and 6 position collapsable stock. Price is firm.

title: For Sale:  Muzzle Brake for your AR or any other platform
postcontent:
If you are looking for a muzzle brake for your AR or Bolt Action rifle , take a look at Grizzly Gun Works . These folks offer some of the most awesome brakes available out there . I was trying to find some one reputable to turn down my bull barrel and then thread and mount a muzzle brake with no luck . I did a little looking around and came across Grizzly's web site and was convinced this might be an alternative . I have ordered a bolt on brake from them and am looking forward to mounting this on my Rock River Arms Varmint Rifle .  Check out their sight , you might find something for your firearm , what ever it might be .  I ordered mine over the phone and Jeff was extremely helpful and patient . I have every confidence what I have ordered will be of the highest quality , so do your self a favor , if you are looking for a solution to muzzle flip as well as esthetically pleasing looks , give a look at their site ! As soon as I apply the brake and have an opportunity to shoot thru it I will post my findings .

Muzzle brake came Saturday , mounted it for before & after pic's then went to the range and ran a few rounds through it .  Right picture is before brake , left picture is after .  Shot the first group then cleaned the bore , applied the brake permanently and shot the second group . This was at 100 yards . Thank you Grizzly Gun Works . I will order a brake from them for a DPMS I have . They offer both threaded and none threaded brakes . $250.00 is what this brake cost , and they do not make the brake for your specific firearm until you place the order .These groups were done quickly to test target reacgusition . Proved to do well !!  This RRA .223 Varmint Gun looks like a .50 Cal. , and that may not be for some people , but for me , looks awesome and shoots the same !!
